6000|$|... "At these words, {{recalling the}} sad {{end of his}} worthy parent, <b>China</b> <b>Aster</b> could not {{restrain}} some tears. Upon which Orchis said: 'Why, <b>China</b> <b>Aster,</b> you are the dolefulest creature. Why don't you, <b>China</b> <b>Aster,</b> take a bright view of life? You will never get on in your business or anything else, if you don't take the bright view of life. It's the ruination of a man to take the dismal one.' Then, gayly poking at him with his gold-headed cane, 'Why don't you, then? Why don't you be bright and hopeful, like me? Why don't you have confidence, <b>China</b> <b>Aster?</b> ...|$|E
